    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="470"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d470">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.00/4–646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        United States Political Adviser for Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 9, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>859. We have been following attentively your telegrams dealing with proposed
                    merger of <gloss target="#t_KPD1">KPD</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_SPD1"
                        >SPD</gloss> and have noted with concern the many indications of pressure,
                    denial of free discussion, and undemocratic methods, employed by those seeking
                    to effect merger. We endorse strongly General Clay’s press statement (<gloss
                        target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 875, Mar 25)<note n="57" xml:id="d470fn57"
                        >See footnote 50, <ref target="#pg_714">p. 714</ref>.</note> that merger
                    will be recognized by US authorities only if demanded by party members rather
                    than a small group of party leaders. We likewise consider entirely proper
                    General Barker’s action approving the <gloss target="#t_SPD1">SPD</gloss> City
                    Convention (<gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 966, Apr 6). We believe that
                    very important issues are involved in matter of <gloss target="#t_SPD1"
                        >SPD</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_KPD1">KPD</gloss> merger and wish to express
                    our unqualified support for position our military authorities have taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
